## Quality Standards

### Source Tiers
| Tier | Description | Examples |
|------|-------------|---------|
| 1 | Official records | Birth/death/marriage certificates, draft cards, SSDI, court records, wills, deeds |
| 2 | Near-contemporary records | Census, church registers, newspapers, city directories |
| 3 | Published genealogies | Books with citations, historical society compilations |
| 4 | Oral history / family documents | Family bibles, personal letters, undated photos |
| 5 | Online trees | Ancestry, FamilySearch, WikiTree, Geni, MyHeritage (leads only) |

### Confidence Levels
- **VERIFIED**: ≥2 independent Tier 1-2 sources, no blocking concerns
- **PROBABLE**: ≥1 Tier 1-3 source with direct evidence
- **POSSIBLE**: Tier 5 / tree-only evidence, or 0 T1-3 sources. Requires `upgrade_path` field.
- **UNVERIFIED**: Not yet researched

**Confidence cannot exceed evidence.** 0 sources = POSSIBLE max regardless of what a prior session set. Any upgrade requires evidence that actually supports the new level.

### Required Source Fields
Every source object in `validation.evidence.sources[]` must have:
```json
{
  "name": "Record title",
  "title": "Collection: Record title",
  "tier": 2,
  "platform": "FamilySearch",
  "type": "census_record",
  "added": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "proves": "birth year, residence",
  "evidence_type": "direct",
  "ark": "https://..."
}
```

