## Automation Gates

### What runs automatically
- Source deduplication and tier classification
- Confidence recalculation after each harvest batch
- Citation standardization
- Research session journaling
- Queue management and priority ordering

### What requires dry-run review before applying
- Any batch write to an external platform (FS, Ancestry, WikiTree)
- GPS remediation patches
- Confidence downgrades

### What requires human attestation
- Conflict resolution when two high-tier sources disagree
- Pre-1700 identity claims (European ancestry is heavily conflated in online trees)
- WikiTree biography edits
- Platform contributions with new parent-child relationships
- Any merge or combination of person records on FamilySearch

### Run order after bulk changes
```
1. gps-element1-remediate.py --apply    # exhaustive search proof
2. gps-element2-remediate.py --apply    # citation standardization
3. gps-compliance-report.py             # fresh GPS audit
4. validate-tree.py --strict            # schema validation
5. reconcile-queue.py                   # platform ID drift check
6. recalculate-confidence.py --dry-run  # REVIEW before --apply
7. recalculate-confidence.py --apply    # promote eligible persons
```

